---
// Calibration — the "stats" section.
// Warm dark background, terracotta brick pattern overlay,
// four big numbers that count up on first reveal.
---

<section class="calibration brick-bg-warm reveal-stagger" id="calibration">
  <div class="calibration__heading">
    <div class="section-label" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">calibrated, not guessed</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">The numbers that earn the name <em style="color: var(--text-accent); font-style: normal">usebrick</em>.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="calibration__stats">
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat__value" data-target="60" data-suffix="+">0</div>
      <div class="stat__label">AI Quality</div>
      <div class="stat__sub">detection rules</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat__value" data-target="13">0</div>
      <div class="stat__label">Engineering Hygiene</div>
      <div class="stat__sub">rules in dimension</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat__value" data-target="4">0</div>
      <div class="stat__label">Security</div>
      <div class="stat__sub">rules in dimension</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat__value" data-target="100" data-suffix="+">0</div>
      <div class="stat__label">Repository Health</div>
      <div class="stat__sub">codebases calibrated</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <blockquote class="calibration__quote">
    Every rule ships with a recall / FP ratio. A rule that fires
    more noise than signal goes back to <em style="color: var(--text-accent); font-style: normal">defaultOff</em>
    until it earns its way on.
    <footer class="calibration__quote-author">— the usebrick calibration contract</footer>
  </blockquote>
</section>
